primary_outcome.description:
Users will report decreased levels of burn out, as measured on the Maslach Burnout Inventory. This scale uses 22 items to assess emotional exhaustion, depersonalization, and measure the sense of personal accomplishment. Higher scores indicate higher, and thus more problematic, levels of burnout. There are 3 scales:
Emotional exhaustion, scores from 0-54 with higher scores indicating more exhaustion;
Depersonalization, scores from 0-30, with higher scores indicating more depersonalization;
Personal achievement, scores from 0-48, with lower scores indicating a worse outcome of less feeling of personal achievement.
